1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:01,960
<i>Rapist! Aah!</i>

2
00:00:02,043 --> 00:00:03,545
- [Kyle grunts]
<i>- Get away from Louisa!</i>

3
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:05,588
- [kick lands]
- [Kyle grunts]<i> Aah!</i>

4
00:00:08,967 --> 00:00:10,260
<i>This is a serious matter.</i>

5
00:00:10,343 --> 00:00:12,429
<i>I'll summon your parents tomorrow.</i>

6
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:16,266
<i>I've agreed with Kyle</i>
<i>and Mr. and Mrs. Sebastian</i>

7
00:00:16,349 --> 00:00:17,726
<i>that you won't be suspended.</i>

8
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:20,061
<i>And they want</i>
<i>the girls to apologize to Kyle.</i>

9
00:00:20,145 --> 00:00:21,354
<i>I'll apologize.</i>

10
00:00:21,438 --> 00:00:24,691
<i>But Mel, Beth and Erica don't have to.</i>
<i>Sorry.</i>

11
00:00:24,774 --> 00:00:27,569
<i>We can still destroy Kyle</i>
<i>even if you don't say anything.</i>

12
00:00:27,652 --> 00:00:29,320
<i>- Wait.</i>
<i>- What happened? Bro?</i>

13
00:00:29,404 --> 00:00:31,489
<i>- Looks like you took a dump!</i>
- [laughter]

14
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:32,741
<i>Jackpot!</i>

15
00:00:32,824 --> 00:00:35,118
<i>- Jackpot!</i>
<i>- Jackpot!</i>

16
00:00:35,201 --> 00:00:36,661
<i>I know you're the ones who humiliated me.</i>

17
00:00:36,745 --> 00:00:39,289
<i>Just wait! I'll get my revenge.</i>

18
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:47,505
[theme music playing]

19
00:01:56,741 --> 00:01:58,827
[Alice] Kyle was so
furious back then, Erica.

20
00:02:00,286 --> 00:02:01,329
Remember?

21
00:02:02,539 --> 00:02:04,624
What if it was him? [exasperated sigh]

22
00:02:04,707 --> 00:02:06,668
What if he really followed
through on his threat to Louisa?

23
00:02:06,751 --> 00:02:12,757
[uneasy music playing]

24
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:17,554
Kyle Sebastian.

25
00:02:19,055 --> 00:02:22,767
[Alice] Uncle Edward said
that they returned to the US immediately

26
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:24,435
after their short stay.

27
00:02:27,188 --> 00:02:29,065
Maybe it was very short because…

28
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:33,278
why didn't anyone know
that they came back here?

29
00:02:36,322 --> 00:02:37,824
[music becomes pensive]

30
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:39,159
I checked.

31
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,578
I looked into Kyle.

32
00:02:42,912 --> 00:02:45,206
If I had known,
I would have checked better.

33
00:02:46,082 --> 00:02:47,500
Hey. We did all we could.

34
00:02:48,084 --> 00:02:49,168
Don't blame yourself.

35
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:53,006
[pensive music continues]

36
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:58,303
Is Uncle Edward sure?

37
00:03:01,222 --> 00:03:04,976
He said he'll try to talk
to Kyle's mom about that.

38
00:03:05,059 --> 00:03:08,605
And about what he was
doing the night that Louisa was killed.

39
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:10,607
She's here.

40
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:12,150
Taking a vacation.

41
00:03:12,233 --> 00:03:14,193
What about his friends?

42
00:03:15,111 --> 00:03:16,738
His former basketball teammates.

43
00:03:16,821 --> 00:03:18,156
I know some of them.

44
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:20,074
They are all in Amurao.

45
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:22,160
I can talk to them tomorrow.

46
00:03:22,243 --> 00:03:23,411
I'll come with you.

47
00:03:23,494 --> 00:03:29,918
[pensive music continues, fades]

48
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:32,295
<i>In my recent press conference,</i>

49
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:35,423
<i>I was finally able to speak my truth.</i>

50
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:37,008
<i>It was hard.</i>

51
00:03:37,091 --> 00:03:39,886
<i>It really took a lot for me to come out</i>

52
00:03:39,969 --> 00:03:41,262
<i>and tell the truth.</i>

53
00:03:42,347 --> 00:03:43,514
<i>But I managed to do it.</i>

54
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:45,600
<i>I did it because I had to.</i>

55
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:49,687
[inhales sharply]
<i>I know my fight doesn't end here.</i>

56
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:52,315
<i>And this is not the hardest part.</i>

57
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:56,945
<i>Because I'm still going</i>
<i>to have to reclaim and rebuild my life.</i>

58
00:03:57,528 --> 00:03:59,364
<i>And from the videos you've seen</i>

59
00:03:59,447 --> 00:04:01,574
<i>of me coming back home…</i>

60
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:03,785
<i>That's only step one.</i>

61
00:04:04,702 --> 00:04:09,499
<i>This isn't just about</i>
<i>me taking back my stuff.</i>

62
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:11,584
<i>This is about me…</i>

63
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:15,880
<i>…opening up and</i>
<i>showing everyone the truth.</i>

64
00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:18,716
<i>I know that…</i>

65
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:21,177
<i>I only have few people on my side.</i>

66
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:23,888
<i>But even though there's just a few of you,</i>

67
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:26,432
<i>I want you to know the truth.</i>

68
00:04:26,975 --> 00:04:28,476
<i>No more secrets.</i>

69
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:31,187
<i>I'm only on day one but…</i>

70
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,606
<i>I feel like a weight's</i>
<i>been lifted off my shoulders.</i>

71
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:35,024
[somber music playing]

72
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:37,568
<i>So this is how it feels</i>
<i>when you aren't hiding anything.</i>

73
00:04:38,486 --> 00:04:41,739
<i>I know people are saying that,</i>

74
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:44,367
<i>my life and career have been ruined.</i>

75
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:46,828
<i>But I refuse to believe that.</i>

76
00:04:47,578 --> 00:04:48,871
<i>I refuse to believe</i>

77
00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:52,792
<i>that people would</i>
<i>rather side with an abuser.</i>

78
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:56,045
<i>And that's why I'm speaking out.</i>

79
00:04:56,546 --> 00:04:58,840
<i>I'm speaking out, not just for me,</i>

80
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:02,802
<i>but for all the women who have been abused</i>

81
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:05,555
<i>and are being abused.</i>

82
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:08,641
<i>Because if I,</i>
<i>someone with the privilege to speak out,</i>

83
00:05:09,851 --> 00:05:12,270
<i>can't get the public's support,</i>

84
00:05:12,895 --> 00:05:14,564
<i>I can't imagine how</i>
<i>much worse it is for them.</i>

85
00:05:15,273 --> 00:05:17,317
[somber music continues]

86
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:21,404
So, to all my followers
who still believe in me,

87
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:23,031
<i>thank you.</i>

88
00:05:24,699 --> 00:05:26,284
<i>From the bottom of my heart.</i>

89
00:05:27,076 --> 00:05:28,661
You and the people I love

90
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:32,040
are the ones who give
me strength to move forward and fight.

91
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:36,377
<i>And because of this new chapter in my life</i>

92
00:05:38,504 --> 00:05:41,049
<i>I've decided to rebrand my channel.</i>

93
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:44,927
[music becomes hopeful]

94
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:50,308
[music turns unsettling]

95
00:05:50,391 --> 00:05:53,478
[Barbara]
Didn't I tell you not to let Mel in?!

96
00:05:54,812 --> 00:05:56,105
Your job was simple!

97
00:05:57,106 --> 00:05:58,232
Idiots!

98
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:00,401
How are you so stupid?!

99
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:02,945
Our instructions were
simple yet you couldn't follow them?!

100
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:04,697
What the fuck?!

101
00:06:04,781 --> 00:06:06,324
- Do you want to lose your--
- [Glaiza] <i>Sir.</i>

102
00:06:06,407 --> 00:06:08,618
I quit.

103
00:06:08,701 --> 00:06:10,620
- What?!
<i>- What I'm saying is…</i>

104
00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:12,163
you don't have to threaten me

105
00:06:12,246 --> 00:06:14,540
<i>because I quit.</i>

106
00:06:14,624 --> 00:06:18,002
I can no longer bear
working for a wife beater!

107
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:22,715
What the fuck did you say?!
You fucking slave! Huh?! [huffing]

108
00:06:22,799 --> 00:06:25,635
You fucking… Fucking bitch!

109
00:06:25,718 --> 00:06:26,761
Fuck!

110
00:06:26,844 --> 00:06:28,888
Who the fuck do you think you are, huh?!

111
00:06:28,971 --> 00:06:31,557
- Anton!
- You're nobody! You're useless!

112
00:06:31,641 --> 00:06:33,768
- Anton! Anton!
- Fuck you! Fuck you!

113
00:06:33,851 --> 00:06:35,019
- Huh?!
- Anton, stop it!

114
00:06:35,103 --> 00:06:36,437
[music fades]

115
00:06:59,585 --> 00:07:01,337
We waited for you to have dinner with us.

116
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:03,131
[sighs]

117
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:06,509
I sent you a text
saying I'd eat at Alice's.

118
00:07:10,138 --> 00:07:12,390
You took that long?

119
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:18,479
It's not easy solving
a 14-year-old murder case.

120
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:24,652
By the way, we have a new suspect.

121
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:28,239
Kyle Sebastian.

122
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:31,951
[sullen music playing]

123
00:07:37,748 --> 00:07:41,502
Are you playing
investigator or are you avoiding me?

124
00:07:41,586 --> 00:07:43,087
- [music fades]
- [sighs]

125
00:07:45,798 --> 00:07:48,259
Can we please talk about it?

126
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:51,846
I was angry that's
why I said all that to Alice.

127
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:55,600
I'm not mad at you. I'm mad at Alice.

128
00:07:55,683 --> 00:07:58,352
Don't people's true feelings
come out when they're angry?

129
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:06,611
[Ryan] I'm sorry.

130
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:10,698
I can't stop feeling this way anymore.

131
00:08:10,781 --> 00:08:13,284
[melancholic music playing]

132
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:15,495
Ever since I heard everything,

133
00:08:16,078 --> 00:08:18,164
I started questioning everything, Beth.

134
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:22,210
If you still love me.

135
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:25,838
If you're still happy.

136
00:08:26,964 --> 00:08:28,716
I just force myself to be okay.

137
00:08:30,218 --> 00:08:34,597
If every night
you think about the life you'd have

138
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:36,349
if we never happened.

139
00:08:39,018 --> 00:08:42,772
If every night you still cry…

140
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:45,942
over the dreams you had to let go of.

141
00:08:46,025 --> 00:08:49,779
[melancholic music continues]

142
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:51,656
Beth, all of that's stuck in my head.

143
00:08:52,573 --> 00:08:53,991
[Ryan sniffles softly]

144
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:56,994
Don't worry…

145
00:08:59,455 --> 00:09:01,165
Maybe I'll be okay someday.

146
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,627
But no matter what happens, Beth,

147
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:08,005
even if you turned into a serial killer,

148
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:13,094
I'd still love you.

149
00:09:15,012 --> 00:09:17,056
[Ryan sniffles] Maybe…

150
00:09:18,057 --> 00:09:19,809
just give me some time.

151
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,813
Let me be for now.

152
00:09:25,773 --> 00:09:27,733
[sniffles] Maybe this….

153
00:09:27,817 --> 00:09:29,902
feeling will pass.

154
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:34,615
[melancholic music continues]

155
00:09:34,699 --> 00:09:37,201
[sniffles, sobs]

156
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:43,874
[Beth sniffles]

157
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:46,961
[sniffles]

158
00:09:47,044 --> 00:09:52,300
[melancholic music continues]

159
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:54,510
[sobs softly]

160
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:00,891
- [music fades]
- [door lock clicks]

161
00:10:04,061 --> 00:10:08,733
[cicadas chirping]

162
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:18,451
Are you okay?

163
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:24,081
[Alice] Marco's right.

164
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:26,542
You're too hard on yourself.

165
00:10:30,338 --> 00:10:32,298
14 years, Alice.

166
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:35,676
For 14 years, I've handled so many cases.

167
00:10:36,886 --> 00:10:39,764
Not once did Louisa's case leave my mind.

168
00:10:42,183 --> 00:10:44,143
[sighs heavily] I thought…

169
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:48,439
I thought I already knew
everything I needed to know.

170
00:10:49,857 --> 00:10:51,233
But Kyle?

171
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:58,407
Kyle. I never even imagined
he was a possibility.

172
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:00,993
[pensive music playing]

173
00:11:01,077 --> 00:11:02,370
[exhales heavily]

174
00:11:02,453 --> 00:11:03,579
Erica…

175
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:08,459
Do you realize how
young we were back then?

176
00:11:09,835 --> 00:11:12,213
How much we went through?

177
00:11:13,839 --> 00:11:17,885
My dad's death, Louisa's murder,

178
00:11:17,968 --> 00:11:20,388
the pressure from the cops, just… just…

179
00:11:20,471 --> 00:11:22,848
the trauma from all of that.

180
00:11:22,932 --> 00:11:24,475
[pensive music continues]

181
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:28,521
God, we were just kids, teenagers.

182
00:11:30,898 --> 00:11:32,191
That was too much.

183
00:11:32,274 --> 00:11:35,903
[pensive music continues]

184
00:11:35,986 --> 00:11:39,365
Think about it. Louisa was dying,

185
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:43,411
we were carrying her, her throat cut.

186
00:11:44,829 --> 00:11:47,498
For us to witness something like that?

187
00:11:47,581 --> 00:11:49,834
We should've at least gone to therapy.

188
00:11:50,751 --> 00:11:51,794
But no.

189
00:11:53,087 --> 00:11:55,798
We didn't get any support at all.

190
00:11:57,341 --> 00:12:00,636
God, that's probably
why we're all so messed up.

191
00:12:00,719 --> 00:12:01,846
[music fades]

192
00:12:01,929 --> 00:12:03,013
Really?

193
00:12:04,348 --> 00:12:05,558
Doesn't seem like it.

194
00:12:06,183 --> 00:12:09,728
[gentle music playing]

195
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:11,522
- [snorts]
- [chuckles]

196
00:12:13,357 --> 00:12:14,817
- Mm.
- [chuckles]

197
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:19,238
[gentle music continues]

198
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:26,912
Are you really okay with
Marco sleeping somewhere else?

199
00:12:27,788 --> 00:12:29,790
I mean, he can sleep here.

200
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:33,836
He can sleep anywhere anyway.

201
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:35,880
It's part of the job.

202
00:12:37,673 --> 00:12:39,008
You and him…

203
00:12:40,217 --> 00:12:41,760
It's complicated.

204
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:49,393
[music becomes unsettling]

205
00:12:49,477 --> 00:12:52,271
[Lucas] <i>Edong,</i>
<i>why do you have Steve's phone?</i>

206
00:12:53,856 --> 00:12:55,441
[Edong] <i>He's not your problem anymore.</i>

207
00:12:55,983 --> 00:12:59,361
[Lucas] <i>Steve has nothing</i>
<i>to do with this! He's my friend!</i>

208
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:01,989
<i>Don't hurt him. Do you hear me?!</i>

209
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:03,699
<i>Edong!</i>

210
00:13:04,783 --> 00:13:07,995
<i>Listen to me, Edong. You need help.</i>

211
00:13:08,078 --> 00:13:09,413
<i>I can help you!</i>

212
00:13:09,497 --> 00:13:10,748
[Yuri groans]

213
00:13:10,831 --> 00:13:13,834
<i>I'm the one who'll help you.</i>

214
00:13:13,918 --> 00:13:16,879
<i>I'm the one who needs to save you.</i>

215
00:13:16,962 --> 00:13:18,464
- [Edong grunts loudly]
- [Lucas] <i>Yuri!</i>

216
00:13:18,547 --> 00:13:19,965
[Edong laughs sinisterly]

217
00:13:20,049 --> 00:13:21,717
- [Yuri groans]
- [Edong] <i>What?</i>

218
00:13:22,259 --> 00:13:24,470
- [Yuri gasping]
- [Edong laughs maniacally]

219
00:13:24,553 --> 00:13:26,680
- [Yuri] <i>No!</i>
- [Lucas] <i>That's not my brother.</i>

220
00:13:29,767 --> 00:13:31,936
[Lucas] <i>He's gone.</i>

221
00:13:32,019 --> 00:13:36,398
[unsettling music continues]

222
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:39,276
- [Alice] What do you mean, complicated?
- [music fades]

223
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:44,281
I don't want relationships.

224
00:13:45,282 --> 00:13:47,034
- What do you mean?
- [clicks tongue]

225
00:13:47,701 --> 00:13:50,246
I mean, I want it…

226
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:52,748
just casual.

227
00:13:53,874 --> 00:13:58,337
No attachments, no expectations.

228
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:01,215
No mess.

229
00:14:04,677 --> 00:14:08,764
Out of all of us, except Louisa,

230
00:14:09,723 --> 00:14:11,475
you were the first to have a boyfriend.

231
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:12,685
[chuckles]

232
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:18,649
And you saw how that turned out, right?

233
00:14:22,069 --> 00:14:24,822
You know, I've always felt guilty about…

234
00:14:24,905 --> 00:14:27,324
how we reacted to you and Lucas.

235
00:14:27,408 --> 00:14:28,868
[gentle music playing]

236
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:31,078
- [sighs] It's okay.
- No.

237
00:14:31,161 --> 00:14:34,874
No, no, no. It's not okay.
I mean, we're your friends.

238
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:37,751
We shouldn't have reacted harshly.

239
00:14:37,835 --> 00:14:39,169
We shouldn't have judged you.

240
00:14:40,588 --> 00:14:43,757
And honestly, I feel even more guilty now

241
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:46,051
when I see the two of you.

242
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:50,264
Especially seeing
the connection you two still have.

243
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:54,977
You and Lucas, I mean…

244
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:59,064
I don't know,
but… the connection is still there.

245
00:15:01,775 --> 00:15:04,695
And I feel guilty all the time

246
00:15:04,778 --> 00:15:07,239
because I know I was one of the reasons

247
00:15:07,323 --> 00:15:09,575
why your relationship got ruined.

248
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:15,497
The connection you're talking about…

249
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:18,125
It's just shared trauma.

250
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:21,670
What if it's not?

251
00:15:23,505 --> 00:15:25,716
What if you're just
really drawn to each other?

252
00:15:25,799 --> 00:15:29,470
[gentle music continues]

253
00:15:37,394 --> 00:15:38,979
[music fades]

254
00:15:39,063 --> 00:15:40,022
[Lucas sniffles]

255
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:41,774
[patrons chatter indistinctly]

256
00:15:42,316 --> 00:15:43,525
[Marco] You're also here, huh?

257
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:49,448
[Marco exhales sharply]

258
00:15:52,201 --> 00:15:53,160
[bottle thuds]

259
00:15:56,163 --> 00:15:57,915
Do you know why I don't trust you?

260
00:15:59,249 --> 00:16:00,709
Because I know… [scoffs]

261
00:16:01,126 --> 00:16:04,797
…if the time comes
that you have to choose between Erica

262
00:16:05,589 --> 00:16:06,590
and your brother…

263
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:11,470
you will still choose your brother.

264
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:16,934
[sullen music playing]

265
00:16:27,903 --> 00:16:29,363
[music fades]

266
00:16:31,699 --> 00:16:33,993
You know, I'm looking for a killer…

267
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:36,161
not a matchmaker.

268
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:40,874
And I think this is better.

269
00:16:42,918 --> 00:16:44,461
I like it better this way.

270
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:46,922
- [somber music playing]
- [Alice] Erica.

271
00:16:47,631 --> 00:16:49,883
Don't shut yourself off from other people…

272
00:16:52,344 --> 00:16:54,930
just because of how
your mother treated you

273
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:57,725
and what we did to you.

274
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:01,103
Don't be afraid…

275
00:17:02,730 --> 00:17:04,273
to trust again

276
00:17:05,149 --> 00:17:06,942
and embrace what you deserve.

277
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:09,695
Because…

278
00:17:10,612 --> 00:17:11,697
you deserve

279
00:17:12,573 --> 00:17:14,199
so much love, Erica.

280
00:17:17,327 --> 00:17:18,579
I hope you know that.

281
00:17:19,288 --> 00:17:24,543
[somber music continues]

282
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:45,105
[music becomes unsettling]

283
00:17:45,189 --> 00:17:49,401
[young Alice sobbing] <i>Mama! Papa!</i>

284
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:52,279
[footsteps approaching]

285
00:17:52,362 --> 00:17:53,697
[door opens]

286
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:57,576
[breathing heavily, gasping]

287
00:17:58,619 --> 00:17:59,620
[grunts]

288
00:18:01,789 --> 00:18:08,796
[unsettling music continues]

289
00:18:13,801 --> 00:18:14,927
What is it?

290
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:16,386
[exhales sharply]

291
00:18:18,138 --> 00:18:19,056
I…

292
00:18:21,016 --> 00:18:22,309
I was there.

293
00:18:22,935 --> 00:18:24,353
I was already there. I…

294
00:18:24,812 --> 00:18:27,981
The door was about to open,
and I was about to find out who took me.

295
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:29,149
[inhales deeply]

296
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:31,193
[exhales sharply]

297
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:34,029
But it always stops there, you know.

298
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:36,031
Right when the door is about to open.

299
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:38,492
Even with my sessions with Doc Isla,

300
00:18:38,575 --> 00:18:39,868
it just stops there.

301
00:18:41,078 --> 00:18:43,455
It's like I'm afraid of finding out.

302
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:45,249
Hey, babe.

303
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:47,459
It's okay.

304
00:18:47,543 --> 00:18:49,044
Don't push yourself too hard.

305
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:53,257
[unsettling music continues]

306
00:18:53,340 --> 00:18:55,217
If I never get over this fear,

307
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:59,221
I'll never find out the truth.

308
00:19:14,778 --> 00:19:15,779
[door opens]

309
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:27,833
[music becomes foreboding]

310
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:59,531
[chilling music playing]

311
00:20:28,810 --> 00:20:34,733
[chilling music continues]

312
00:20:50,249 --> 00:20:55,295
[chilling music continues]

313
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:13,272
<i>After14 years, they found out</i>
<i>that Kyle returned to Amurao.</i>

314
00:21:13,355 --> 00:21:14,439
<i>But I didn't say anything.</i>

315
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:15,899
<i>I know how to keep a secret.</i>

316
00:21:15,983 --> 00:21:18,610
<i>That was a long time ago.</i>
<i>Why are you still bugging Kyle?</i>

317
00:21:18,694 --> 00:21:20,028
<i>He threatened Louisa that day.</i>

318
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:21,989
<i>You want to prove that Edong is innocent,</i>

319
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:23,907
<i>so now, you're looking for</i>
<i>someone else to take the blame.</i>

320
00:21:23,991 --> 00:21:27,160
<i>Aah! Why? Why? Why me?</i>

321
00:21:27,244 --> 00:21:30,622
[laughs maniacally] <i>Is this another trial?</i>

322
00:21:30,706 --> 00:21:34,626
<i>Angels send demons to protect sinners.</i>

323
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:36,420
[Beth] <i>All our lives are in danger now,</i>

324
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:38,046
<i>as well as our loved ones.</i>

325
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:40,048
<i>We have to stop Edong.</i>

326
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:41,842
[knocking on door]

327
00:21:43,135 --> 00:21:44,261
<i>Bunny!</i>

328
00:21:44,344 --> 00:21:45,345
<i>Hello.</i>

329
00:21:46,388 --> 00:21:50,517
<i>I won't stop until</i>
<i>I finish what I have to do.</i>

330
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:51,518
<i>Aah!</i>
